2 Exploratory data analysis

In this project, I inversitgated over 150 river stations in europe, and issuses relating to changes in seasonal discharge, particularly after 1980

stations are located in europe, particularly density of location in mainland western europe and scandinavia, there are some stations sparely distributed in Russia and eastern europe, and the British Isles and Iceland.

2.1.3 Distribution in space of stations

There is a large cluster of stations around 45-50 degrees in latitude and 5 to 15 degrees in longitude, theses would correspond to rivers mainly flowing out of alpine regions in Switzerland and Germany, with higher altitudes, as latitude increases, the altitude decreases, this is typical of Germany, since the coastline is in the north.

2.2.2 catergorisation of the data

After calculating the minimum and maximum run off for each year for each station, I plotted the maximum value and minimum value and made categories for the data. I also categorised by altitude, though some records were missing.

2.3 Five chsoen rivers

2.3.1 Five rivers

Danube river-bratislava, while there are no dams between Vienna and Bratislava, the danube has many dams in its upper channel and just past the station there is a dam, there has been lots of conflict between Slovakia and hungary on wheter further interventions should take place

rhine upper parts of the rhine have many dams sitter 11 hydroelectric plants along the river luestan- a small river heading to a lkae, in high altitude influenced heavily by snowmelt glama many power stations have been built along the river.

I chose stations based on large mean values, large standard deviations, large altitude, high latitude, and high max values, were duplicate rivers were chosen, another station which a smaller value was chosen
